pageContext.description: A fragment of a copper alloy Bronze Age socketed axehead or socketed chisel dating from about 1000 BC - 700 BC. It has a fairly straight cutting edge with rounded corners one of which is broken off. There are straight but tapering sides and an ancient break at the top across the end of the socket where it is rectangular in cross-section. The rest of the tool is missing. The fragment has a green and brown mottled patina. the fragment is too small to classify. It could be a small socketed axe, a palstave or a chisel. It is similar to SWYOR-AC278F, SF-9E9143 and NCL-F12C3E. The fragment is 27.3mm long, 33.2mm wide and 12.4mm thick. 41.3g.
